{
  "stem": "8786.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And unfortunately, when they realized it, it was too late.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And those days, there was plenty, plenty time yet to do something about it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was-- that was number one.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They took away the business license.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Jewish doctors, I think-- Jewish boys couldn't attend any more universities.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the source of parnassah or livelihood shrunk.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So many, many people were supported by the local-- by the local synagogue.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Larger families were-- Jewish people who used to go to their own businesses, all of a sudden they became-- they went out to the wood, to the forest, they're chopping wood.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They did work which was not their profession, just to survive.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I'll never forget that we did something also, a beautiful thing which was-- the credit belongs to my father.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We-- he created a-- a source of parnassah not for us only, a livelihood for probably about four, five families.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He found that-- he had connections with a big factory, and he brought home big, big pieces of carpets.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And from the carpets, we took apart the carpets.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And from those strings in the carpet, each of the carpet, the string actually was twisted from five thin pieces of thread, just like you have a [INAUDIBLE], if I may compare it to it.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we took that apart, home, in the house.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Boys and girls were doing it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We took this apart and made-- it was wool.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we made from these [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] wool for knitting, yarn.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "From carpets, you took apart the carpets and took it to small pieces and thin pieces.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we tied it together and it was a beautiful cones of yarns.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
